@startuml Training_Plans_Component_Diagram

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam wrapWidth 180
skinparam maxMessageSize 180
skinparam linetype ortho

title Training Plans - System Component Diagram

actor Athlete
actor Coach
actor Admin

package "Client Applications" {
  [Web Frontend\nReact + TypeScript + Mantine] as FE
  [Mobile App\nExpo / React Native] as MOBILE
}

package "Backend Platform\nFastAPI + SQLAlchemy" {
  [API Entry / Router Layer] as API

  [Identity & Membership Component\nauth, users, profiles, coach-athlete links, organizations] as C_ID

  [Training Planning Component\ncalendar, workouts, season plans, day notes] as C_PLAN

  [Activity Processing Component\nuploads, parsing, dedupe, compliance, personal records] as C_ACTIVITY

  [Communications Component\nactivity threads, comments, organization messaging] as C_COMMS

  [Integrations & Wellness Component\nprovider connections, sync state, webhooks, wellness imports] as C_INT

  [Authorization & Permissions Component] as C_PERM

  [Support & Notification Component\nfeedback and outbound email] as C_NOTIFY
}

package "Persistence" {
  database "PostgreSQL\ncore domain data" as DB
  folder "File Storage\nuploads/activities, uploads/chat" as FILES
}

package "External Systems" {
  [OAuth / Provider APIs\nStrava, Garmin, WHOOP, Polar, Suunto, COROS] as EXT_PROVIDERS
  [Health Bridge Sources\nApple Health, Google Fit] as EXT_BRIDGES
  [Webhook Sources] as EXT_WEBHOOKS
  [SMTP / Email Service] as EXT_SMTP
}

Athlete --> FE
Coach --> FE
Admin --> FE
Athlete --> MOBILE
Coach --> MOBILE

FE --> API : HTTP / JSON
MOBILE --> API : HTTP / JSON

API --> C_ID
API --> C_PLAN
API --> C_ACTIVITY
API --> C_COMMS
API --> C_INT

C_ID --> C_PERM
C_PLAN --> C_PERM
C_ACTIVITY --> C_PERM
C_COMMS --> C_PERM
C_INT --> C_PERM

C_ACTIVITY --> C_PLAN : matches completed activities\nto planned workouts
C_COMMS --> C_ID : resolves athlete / coach / org membership
C_INT --> C_ACTIVITY : imports activities and wellness data
C_NOTIFY --> C_ID
C_COMMS --> C_NOTIFY : send support / notification email

C_ID --> DB
C_PLAN --> DB
C_ACTIVITY --> DB
C_COMMS --> DB
C_INT --> DB
C_PERM --> DB
C_NOTIFY --> DB

C_ACTIVITY --> FILES : activity file uploads
C_COMMS --> FILES : chat attachments

C_INT --> EXT_PROVIDERS : OAuth, sync, provider REST APIs
EXT_WEBHOOKS --> C_INT : webhook callbacks
EXT_BRIDGES --> C_INT : bridge ingestion payloads
C_NOTIFY --> EXT_SMTP : outbound email

note right of C_ID
  Primary implementation anchors:
  routers/auth.py, routers/users.py,
  auth.py, services/permissions.py

  Owns the identity and membership domain:
  User, Profile, ProfileMetricHistory,
  CoachAthleteLink, Organization,
  OrganizationMember.
end note

note right of C_PLAN
  Primary implementation anchors:
  routers/calendar.py, routers/planning.py,
  routers/workouts.py, services/season_planner.py,
  workout_templates.py

  Owns PlannedWorkout, PlannedWorkoutVersion,
  StructuredWorkout, SeasonPlan, DayNote.
end note

note right of C_ACTIVITY
  Primary implementation anchors:
  routers/activities.py, parsing.py,
  services/compliance.py,
  services/activity_dedupe.py,
  services/personal_records.py

  Owns Activity ingestion and analysis,
  including matching against planned workouts.
end note

note right of C_COMMS
  Primary implementation anchors:
  routers/communications.py, routers/admin.py,
  services/support.py

  Owns CommunicationThread,
  CommunicationComment,
  CommunicationAcknowledgement,
  OrganizationGroupMessage,
  OrganizationCoachMessage,
  OrganizationDirectMessage.
end note

note right of C_INT
  Primary implementation anchors:
  routers/integrations.py,
  routers/integrations/*,
  integrations/service.py,
  integrations/registry.py,
  integrations/ingest.py,
  integrations/crypto.py,
  integrations/connectors/*

  Owns ProviderConnection,
  ProviderSyncState,
  ProviderWebhookEvent,
  IntegrationAuditLog,
  HRVDaily, RHRDaily,
  SleepSession, StressDaily.
end note

legend left
  This diagram is a system-level component view.
  It groups runtime responsibilities into major platform components
  and shows the main dependencies between clients, backend domains,
  persistence, and external systems.
endlegend

@enduml
